=head1 DESCRIPTION

Summarizes the resource sets used in a policy.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Description => Str

A description of the resource set.


=head2 Id => Str

A unique identifier for the resource set. This ID is returned in the
responses to create and list commands. You provide it to operations
like update and delete.


=head2 LastUpdateTime => Str

The last time that the resource set was changed.


=head2 Name => Str

The descriptive name of the resource set. You can't change the name of
a resource set after you create it.


=head2 ResourceSetStatus => Str

Indicates whether the resource set is in or out of an admin's Region
scope.

=over

=item *

C<ACTIVE> - The administrator can manage and delete the resource set.

=item *

C<OUT_OF_ADMIN_SCOPE> - The administrator can view the resource set,
but they can't edit or delete the resource set. Existing protections
stay in place. Any new resource that come into scope of the resource
set won't be protected.

=back




